HEADWORD: Guacho
<hw>Gua"cho</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Guachos</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr></plu> <ety>[Spanish American.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>One of the mixed-blood (Spanish-Indian) inhabitants of
the pampas of South America; a mestizo.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An Indian who serves as a messenger.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Guaco</ent>⟦br⟧
